          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Singapore, 5/12/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.75)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9935'>Gerald "tangent" Tan</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9935&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 21, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> So here am I, going into my first tournament and I&#39;m naturally nervous about it. I stayed up late the night before trying to decide between two decks to play, with a choice between a Dwarf/Moria deck and a Ranger+Hobbit/Uruk running deck. Finally I decided to play both decks against each other and the dwarf deck emerged the winner, thanks to timely appearances of the Cave Troll (sites 2 and 7). I didn&#39;t quite like it, but I decided to go ahead and play the dwarf/Moria deck in the tournament. Well, it&#39;s just for the fun and experience isn&#39;t it?<br>
<br>
My Dwarf/Moria deck is very similar to Devonator&#39;s &quot;Moria Family Album&quot; deck. I will probably post a deck list soon, but please refer to his deck list if you wish. Devon and I have been discussing tech via d-mail for the past few weeks resulting in a few modifications. Mainly in the fellowship side, we&#39;ve added in 2x Gimli&#39;s Helm and dropped the PATHSs. I&#39;ve added Mithril Coat and Bounder. In the shadow side, we&#39;ve dropped a troll hammer in favour of moria axe (works great with the keyward), and added in 2x Relics of Moria. I dropped something else in favour of a 2nd Keyward (he&#39;s just too gosh darnit useful).<br>
<br>
The tournament started about half an hour late with 14 players which was kind of a small turnout. Notable players like Frankie Poh and David Feng were not playing, and the pre-tournament favourites seem to be Yeo Leck Koon and Lee Tze Ming who took first and second places in the previous tournament. So we were paired up and my first game...<br>
<br>
<br>
Game 1 vs Amos Khoo, Big Fellowship + Uruks<br>
<br>
Amos bidded 2 to my 0, started Legolas and Arwen, pulled Aragorn with the Pony, played Gimli and made it easily through my Trollshaw and Council Courtyard with my hand full of fellowship cards. My turn I pulled Aragorn with the Pony, played Farin, loaded up the dwarves with their possesions. Moving out, I faced 2 Uruks, which only meant one thing.. it&#39;s time to get Aragorn and Farin killed as soon as possible and hope Fror comes along quickly enough. Aragorn took his 2 wounds while Farin was overwhelmed. Fortunately, Savagery was not played allowing me to move again to Council Courtyard where Aragorn volunteered to take on Uruks while Gloin took 2 damage from a third Uruk which joined the party.<br>
<br>
My Moria engine was slow to set up thanks to bad draws and his big fat Gandalf was sleeping away the conditions which I setup. Balrog ate his Gimli and Merry but the rest of his fellowship is still going strong. I managed to pull Sam and Fror out before reaching the sanctuary just after him. Cave Troll plus a few other biggies stopped his fellowship at Anduin Wilderlands so there is a glimmer of hope, but Lurtz and Troops and another Uruk stopped me there too, despite my fellowship coming together with the 3 big dwarves almost fully equipped. I was able to spot the 5 orcs to stop him at Shores and was forced to make a double move for the win. He played three Uruks at slopes of which I was only able to kill one. Praying that he has an all-fellowship hand, I ran into the Slopes but out popped a Lieutenant and a Captain, and then another Uruk from the discard pile. I conceded with nothing to save Frodo.<br>
<br>
FL +1<br>
<br>
Pretty sad, I just lost my first tournament game and I thought it was kind of close. The big mistake I made was discarding my only Bounder to They Are Coming sometime in Moria just to get out an extra runner which was going to get slaughtered anyway. That Bounder could have saved me at the Slopes, but then again they were all 9 strength Uruks and Frodo with Sting can&#39;t handle 2 of them. Still, if only one of them was an Uruk Fighter I would have made it<br>
<br>
Slops: <br>
- Lost my first tournament game<br>
- Discarding only Bounder... never do that again!<br>
- No PATHS in my deck... but this deck can&#39;t do with any hand-choke cards, really<br>
- Uruks. Always forcing me to small fellowships<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
- Ermm... I got some experience?<br>
<br>
Not much surprise from the other games, except that Lee Tze Ming lost to a relative new player playing a Dwarf/Moria deck which was short of the rares it really need. So anyway the pairings came up and I was to play against....<br>
<br>
<br>
Game 2 vs Lee Tze Ming, Big Fellowship + Uruks<br>
<br>
Hmm.. so he lost to a deck like mine in the first round while I lost to a deck like his. This should be interesting. He bidded 3 to my 0 to go first, revealing the starting fellowship of Legolas and Gimli, pulled Sam with Green Dragon Inn, Gandalf with his staff, Elrond, Albert Dreary, rare Merry and a partridge in a pear tree. All I had in my hand was a They Are Coming and together with the Goblin Swarms I drew on reconciling, that was all I played (and promptly lost to Albert Dreary) while he took a stroll to my Council Courtyard. I pulled Sam using Green Dragon Inn, played my entire fellowship hand including Fror and Aragorn and had to stop at 2 when 2 Uruks came out. Aragorn exerted to take on both and died and both were Savageried, meaning Sam had to die and Gimli took 2 wounds, thus I was stopped at Trollshaw Forest. I was almost ready to concede this match with this really bad start and feeling down about losing the first match, knowing that it would be hard for my underworking shadow to stop his big Sleep-laden fellowship.<br>
<br>
He moved into Moria Stairway and I was able to pull out a few minions to challenge him but he dealt with them no problem, choosing to stop as he was ahead in the race anyway. I pulled a surprise on him though, playing and drawoing lots of 0 cost possessions before moving into the Council Courtyard, giving him 4 twilight. Naturally he couldn&#39;t play anything. I then moved passed Sanctuary into Moria Stairway, removing 2 twilight for Council Courtyard, adding 4 for campanions and 0 for the underground site (no longer regret the change to the MoM Gimli) and he only had one Uruk to show for it which wasn&#39;t a problem, I took 2 wounds on Fror which will be healed next turn thanks to 2 Durin Wakes. <br>
<br>
On his fellowship, Gandalf slept away the conditions, he played Rareagorn and rare Pippin and moved, giving me enough twilight to play just about my entire shadow hand including Keyward with Moria Axe, Cave Troll and the Balrog Flame of Udon. Aragorn exerts to them them all, and in the fierce skirmish, Gandalf exhausts to cancel and Pippin was fed to the Cave Troll like all that he is really good for. Naturally he stopped. I moved into the Bridge without much trouble but decided to stop to allow my Dimrill Dale to be played.<br>
<br>
Back to his fellowship at the Bridge, he played Hobbit-loving Boromir, but couldn&#39;t Sleep because Gandalf is exhausted. So he Stings me and moves, giving me 10 twilight while I see a Cave Troll and Enquea in my hand. With 3 Armories and Relics in play, there was no problem playing both together with hordes of other goblins. During the manouevre, I see Legolas with 1 wound, exhausted Gandalf, Merry with 1 wound, Boromir fresh and Gimli with 1 wound. With the three shots I have, I wounded Legolas to exhaust him, wounded Merry to make sure he can&#39;t pump anyone, and finally Gandalf bites the dust. After he assigned whatever he could, I assigned the rest to make sure all the campanions die before Enquea and Cave Troll came back to finish Frodo up in the fierce skirmish for my very first<br>
<br>
FW +4<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
- W00t! My first tournament win!<br>
- Moria engine started late but still worked fine<br>
- Enquea finally did something useful<br>
- Site 3 + 4 denial. Heh.<br>
<br>
Slops<br>
- Tze Ming having a bad day I guess<br>
- Bad start<br>
<br>
Kelvin the TD was complaining about the number of 1-1s he has to assign pairings to (well, what do you expect anyway?) The 3 players at 2-0 are Leck Koon (Shoulder fire + Moria swarms) and my friends Yunnshing (Big fellowship + Uruks... see a pattern here?) and Eugene (Ranger + Sauron). Leck Koon was paired down while my 2 friends were paired against each other while I was paired with...<br>
<br>
<br>
Game 3 vs Loh Mun Kit, Hobbit orgy + Moria<br>
<br>
So he bidded something to my 0 and pulled the Gaffer with Bag End, while I groaned seeing his fellowship. For some reason my deck never had much success against those pesky hobbits who are somehow always able to pump themselves to avoid being overwhelmed. He played the usual hobbit stuffs and ran to 3 without any problems, burning a couple of stealth cards, and I did the same. I was of course happy to see Moria being played and as you know, dwarves with Stairs own Moria. <br>
<br>
At my Moria Stairway, Mun Kit lost Pippin to the cave troll, burning another Hobbit Stealth. He stopped while I slaughtered everything in the dwarves way at the stairway and ran into the bridge facing little resistance. At the bridge, he lost Merry to the Balrog and Sam to the many minions I piled on him (lesson I learnt from previous games. Always make sure Sam is killed first before trying to overwhelm Frodo). Frodo was able to survive the Balrog with an Intuition and Bounder. I moved easily into Dimrill Dale while his Frodo was inevitably overwhelmed by the swarms there for a<br>
<br>
FW +7<br>
<br>
Props<br>
- My dwarves owning Moria like they should<br>
- My Moria side working like it should<br>
<br>
Slops<br>
- I didn&#39;t remember much of the details of this game<br>
- Mun Kit really needs some condition removal in his deck<br>
<br>
Leck Koon and Eugene won their games and were paired for the showdown. They finished their 3rd round early and were already playing their last round together before the rest of the 4th round pairings were announced. Leck Koon went first and had his hand entirely fellowship. So did Eugene. Naturally Leck Koon had a free ride into the first sanctuary and so did Eugene. At the sanctuary, Leck Koon had his shoulder-fire engine completely set up with 2 Secret Sentinels in hand. Eugene was ready to play the Orc Bowmen and Under The Watching Eyes in his hands when the final round pairings were called.<br>
<br>
<br>
Game 4 vs Evan Goh, Hobbits/Gimli denial + Moria<br>
<br>
I groaned finding out who I was paired against. I playtested my deck the night before against him and no matter how many minions I pile up on those pesky hobbits, he always have enough pumps. I was almost ready to concede there and there but I decided to just try anyway. So he bidded 4 to my 0, started Hobbiton Party Fields, pulled Bilbo, and was on his way, moving to 3 and basically ignoring the few minions I played. On my turn I went into my draw deck for Bilbo then remembered I took him out the night before because I wasn&#39;t expecting Sauron players in the tournament. So I made it to 3 despite a pretty small fellowship.<br>
<br>
His denial engine was helping him well through Moria and I couldn&#39;t play the Cave Troll in my hand, so he ran through to the bridge. Deciding against the Balrog, I played the keyward and Cave Troll, together with other minions. Gimli was slaughtered by the Cave Troll (well, there isn&#39;t any more underground after the bridge, I suppose) and Filiberted on the second round. On my turn I moved into the bridge without much trouble.<br>
<br>
He moved into Dimril Dale, where I played loads of minions and piled up the excess on Sam who managed to survive everything with Intuitions and Bounder. Arggh... To put the pressure on him, I moved passed the sanctuary into his Wilderlands. On his turn, he raced into Wilderlands and again I piled up all my minions on Sam and this time they broke through, killing Sam. I stacked everyone on the swarms. Then he did something amazing. Knowing that he can&#39;t stop my fellowship from moving to 8 and 9, he continued on with his lone Frodo to my Shores! Again, I played all the minions I can, loading everything up on Frodo. 2 PATHS and they were all cleared despite sacrificing 2 Armories. On my turn, he got out the 5 orcs he need to stop me at the Shores and so it leads to the final showdown, his Frodo moving into the Summit.<br>
<br>
Bilbo exerted twice, discarding a Consorting with Wizard and an O Elbereth Gilthoniel to discard my Swarms (together with 4 minions on them) and my They Are Coming. This is not looking good as I drew a hand with just a Host of Thousands, Guard Commander and an Armoury, and 10 twilight. I used the site text to draw 2 more cards. Another fellowship card and a scimitar. Without much of a choice, I played the Armory, Guard Commander and Scimitar and pulled a fellowship card. With 8 twilight left, I hosted for a Scavenger and Scimitar leaving me with 6 Twilight. Only one card can save me now, and I pulled it.. They Are Coming! With 6 cards left in hand and 3 twilight, I pulled a Goblin Runner and Ancient Chieftain out of the discard pile and hoped for the best.<br>
<br>
At the skirmish, he played his 3rd PATHS, and I saved the Scavenger with my only Armory left. Evan played 2 Hobbit Stealths and it&#39;s time to add up the strengths. Frodo with Sting and 2 Stealths is 10, so I would need 30 strength with Bounder to overwhelm him. Scavenger with Scimitar is 10, Guard Commander with Scimitar is 9, and Ancient Chieftain with his 2 friends is 11, for the magical total of 30 and a<br>
<br>
FW +10<br>
<br>
Evan was understandably upset as he thought he made it. In fact I thought he made it too. He played well and really didn&#39;t deserve to lose. He could have won by not discarding O Elbereth! Gilthoniel! but really that was the correct thing to do.<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
- Probably the best and most exciting gave I&#39;ve ever played<br>
- Drew They Are Coming at the right time<br>
<br>
Slops<br>
- Evan played a great game but had to lose<br>
<br>
<br>
The top pair finished their game early and the result wasn&#39;t a surprise considering how the game started, with Leck Koon winning the tournament at 4-0. Yunnshing won his last game, so that makes three of us at 3-1, with me naturally having the lowest Strength of Schedule for fourth place and Eugene taking second place.<br>
<br>
Well, although it started out bad, the whole tournament turned out pretty ok. I guess I should be happy with the 3-1 considering it&#39;s my first tournament. So to sum up the entire tournament<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
- Did pretty decently for my first tournament<br>
- Learnt a few lessons (never discard Bounder!)<br>
<br>
Slops<br>
- Sorry about screwing your ratings, guys. I didn&#39;t mean it... really!<br>
<br>
<br>
There was one game left remaining and they were still at the bridge (geez!!), between Tze Ming (now at 0-3, apparently he was having a VERY BAD day) and Celia. But he had fun nevertheless in this last game as I watched his Boromir double-pump Merry to 9, who pumps Gandalf with from 9 to 18, who triple-Servants the Cave Troll with Hammer from 18 to 9, &quot;clobrinthe Cave Troll. The two of them bicker over his inappropriate words used in front of a lady (well.. Celia insists on being called a girl... but anyway) while I think of other ways of handling the Cave Troll with Hammer.<br>
<br>
Tze Ming finally got his win, so I stayed around and played a couple of games with him with &#39;the decks we really should have played in the tournament&#39;. My Ranger/Uruk deck had beaten Leck Koon&#39;s deck in practice the day before. Tze Ming&#39;s alternatate deck was a Big Fellowship with a hybrid Sauron-Moria hybrid archery shadow which killed my fellowship both games we played. Tze Ming moaned about how the results might have been different if he had used that deck instead.<br>
<br>
Oh well, all in all, a very interesting experience, this tournament. Looking forward to the next one (which I am free to attend... arghhh) <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3677&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
